The paper proposes a novel technique for training deep networks to obtain feature representations that exhibit strong clustering behavior in a Euclidean space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
